          <actions />
          <lines>
            <line character="Cape" startTime="22" pace="0.8203957">Did it even happen? Sure it happened. It happened, I’m not crazy, I know! I arrived at the Bloor Street bridge, and I climbed up on the wall, right? And I was gonna do it, I was just about to jump when I heard this drum sound, as if the whole city knew, boom boom boom boom BOOM BOOM BOOM BOOM BOOM BOOM (speaks in small strange voice) “I’m not gonna hurt you.”</line>
            <line character="Cape" startTime="41" pace="1">Who’s that? A cop? There’s nobody! Just! A white dog! Beside me! How did it…</line>
            <line character="Cape" startTime="46" pace="1">“YOU’RE JUMPING TO HELL” the dog, the dog spoke.</line>
            <line character="Cape" startTime="49" pace="2">So I…answered-</line>
            <line character="Cape" startTime="50.5" pace="1">“BUT I’M LIVING IN HELL…ANYWAY.”</line>
            <line character="Cape" startTime="52.5" pace="0.75">“YOU’RE LIVING IN HELL, ‘CAUSE YOU AIN’T DONE YOUR MISSION.”</line>
            <line character="Cape" startTime="55" pace="2">“WHAT’S THAT?”</line>
            <line character="Cape" startTime="56.5" pace="0.65">“TO SAVE YOUR FATHER FROM DEATH, TO SAVE YOUR FATHER FROM DEATH.”</line>
            <line character="Cape" startTime="59" pace="1">The dog…spoke! I’m not kidding! This dog actually spoke she saved me from the plunge; it was the weirdest-</line>
            <line character="Glidden" startTime="65" pace="5.533333">OUT OF THE TUNNEL, […]</line>
          </lines>
